Maybe secure, not private, scammy. Requires your phone number, so it couldn't possibly be private (unless they did a scheme like Threema, and they don't) ... Also obviously sending to a sms will be grossly insecure(not end2end encrypted), which isnt made clear. My ToS was in German as far as I could...Full ReviewMaybe secure, not private, scammy. Requires your phone number, so it couldn't possibly be private (unless they did a scheme like Threema, and they don't) ... Also obviously sending to a sms will be grossly insecure(not end2end encrypted), which isnt made clear. My ToS was in German as far as I could discern, which isn't legally binding in my country (I don't understand German). Don't use this app, you'd have to be a complete idiot to use this software as security software. The company likely has ill intent otherwise, why lie?
